messages.title: REDUCE RAIL FARES BY 10%, SAYS LEADER NATALIE BENNETT
messages.content: Leader Natalie Bennett has announced that if the Green Party were in charge, they'd commit to lowering rail fares by at least 10 percent.

messages.title: 8,000 COUNCIL HOMES LOST IN “REGENERATION” OF HOUSING ESTATES, REPORT REVEALS
messages.content: The report demonstrates the loss of council homes due to 'regeneration' projects, an issue the Green Party pledges to counteract by focusing on people's needs over private profit.

keyPolicies.policyDescription: Propose a 10% reduction in rail fares.
Countering the loss of council homes due to regeneration projects by emphasizing the needs of people over private profits.
